      "agentMessaged": {
        "agentMessage": "I have been trying to checkout and analyze the 'observabilitystack' controllers, but I keep running into issues exploring the codebase due to missing files and branches in the repository structure. Specifically, the path `observabilitystack/backend/src/main/java/com/microsaas/observabilitystack/controller` initially didn't exist or wasn't tracked properly.\n\nI have found the controllers on the main branch using a temporary clone, but due to a massive number of unignored changes in the workspace (likely node_modules or similar generated code), commands to explore the project structure are triggering diff size warnings. \n\nTo fix the observabilitystack architecture:\n1. I have identified 7 controllers: AlertController, DashboardController, HealthCheckController, IncidentController, MockObservabilityController, OnCallController, SLOController.\n2. I need to move business logic from these controllers to `@Service` classes in the `.../service/` package.\n3. Then refactor controllers to delegate to services and return `ResponseEntity`, ensuring controller methods are max 5 lines.\n4. Add `@Transactional` on service methods that write to DB.\n5. Write 2 unit tests per new service class.\n\nCould you advise on how I can proceed in a clean environment? The git diff warnings are making it tricky to manipulate the repo state, and I want to ensure I'm using the exact branch state you expect for creating the PR. I recommend we update `.gitignore` or `git clean -xfd` in the root correctly before making changes, but any advice on branch / environment setup would be very helpful."
